args: The town is really starting to look\nlike its old self again.
It's true that the building repairs\nare almost complete...
However, I fear the entire town\nstill has a rather gloomy air.
Well, they WERE just attacked by fiends;\nno one can blame people for feeling low.
Buildings can be repaired, but alas,\nhearts are not so easily mended.
I wonder if there's something we can do\nto cheer them... Hmm? What's that?
Someone has collapsed on the ground!
Grub? Wait, do you think he\ncollapsed out of hunger?
I've been helping out at a nearby café.\nLet us take him there, quickly!
I've never seen anyone eat so fast.\nHe even puts Ranzal to shame!
I owe you two big time.
We're just glad to see you up and well.
But what were you doing lying\non the ground to begin with?
I heard a rumor about a town\nthat was attacked by fiends.
I started making my way there\nand must'a forgotten to eat.
I wasn't aware eating was something\none could simply ＂forget＂ to do.
So far as I know, this is the only town\nin the area that's been attacked lately.
Well, guess I made it safely. Nice.
If you call ending up collapsed\non the ground ＂safe,＂ then yes.
Still, what drove you to come here and—
No, I'm leaving this town, and that's that!\nFiends have already come for us once,\nso who's to say they won't do it again?!
But all people keep talking about is how\nsafe and prosperous Chanzelia is!
What's wrong with wanting to live\nsomewhere you can feel safe?
But ever since those fiends came,\nthis town's population has been\nshrinking by the day.
At this rate, it's only a matter of time\nbefore we dry up and blow away!
Please, you must stay here and help\nget our town back on its feet!
Nothing you say will change my mind.\nI'm outta here.
Ah, Your Highness. My sincere apologies\nfor disturbing you with all of that.
It sounds like that man is leaving?
Him and many others besides, I fear.
I understand how they feel, but if everyone\nleaves, this town has no future.
We're SO close to rebuilding everything!
Do you have some manner of plan?
I sure do: We're gonna have a FESTIVAL!
Yep! Oh, the name's Yaten, and I'm a\nfestival planner from over in Hinomoto.
I've been traveling around and livening up\ntowns with festivals for a long while now.
You do that? As in, for a career?
Yep! Look, people leave towns because\nthey don't feel like they have a future\nthere, right?
My festivals are all about giving people\nhope in their hometown again.
Nothing brings light to the world\nlike a good festival!
Please, sir! You must arrange one of\nthese hope festivals with all speed!
If you really think this will work,\nyou're welcome to use our castle\nas your base of operations.
This man is a prince of Alberia.\nHe rules over a castle in the Mistholt.
I'll be happy to help however I can.
Huh. You're a real big shot.
Then will you plan a festival for us?
Sure, why not? It'll be a kick in the... Huh?
Where the hell have you BEEN, Yaten?!
You're here just in time, Natalie.\nBecause guess what...
Why'd you say the same thing as me?
Guess we're just on the same wavelength.
Well, you're right—the boss man here\nasked me to throw together a festival.
Then let's make it a festival these\nfolks ain't never gonna forget!
Ha! This burg's gonna be up and\nfull of life in no time!
